{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#3562: No forceUpdate() in Vue 3 with compositionAPI",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:27:48.429675+00:00",
  "text": "No forceUpdate() in Vue 3 with compositionAPI\n\n### Version\r\n3.0.11\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[https://jsfiddle.net/posva/km2qpwx7/](https://jsfiddle.net/posva/km2qpwx7/)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\nIn Vue2 we can call this.$forceUpdate() to force update a component. Once I switched to Vue 3 Composition API, seems this feature is lost... How can I get it back?\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\nI can call $forceUpdate()\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\nI cannot call $forceUpdate()\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
